    {
      "charEnd": 3815,
      "charStart": 815,
      "factId": "hz.web.5beefc4e30a03ff3.fact.13",
      "kind": "bullet",
      "text": "No portion of this layout and contents should be reproduced, plagiarized, or duplicated in any manner. * ============================================================================================== ---> &#8988; disclosure. &#8991; &#10023; cradle of the astralspire network update log Home &#9702; About &#9702; Archives &#9702; Aelysia Welcome to Disclosure , the update log for Aelysia.net . Like any long-term project, I aim to keep a record of the activities and key changes made on this domain. This log serves as a space to track announcements and general updates. All entries are archived on a single page, allowing for easier navigation through individual categories. Please note that as you explore older entries, some links may be outdated or no longer accessible. Where Colors Meet Posted on 13 Feb '26 filed under Aquarel.nu , New We've opened a new wing within Aquarel—a directory devoted to web cliques we've encountered and quietly admired. Aquarel speaks to watercolor: pigment meeting water, edges softening, colors blending into one another without losing their character. This extension follows that same spirit. It began as a separate idea, something we thought would live outside the network. But keeping it within Aquarel felt more honest. We don't exist in isolation; we flow alongside other communities, influences gently bleeding into one another. Each listing includes a small note&mdash;just enough to capture a clique’s tone, focus, or creative texture. Inspired in part by the thoughtful presentation style of Cloudplane , the directory isn't just a list of links. It's a wash of shared affinities, layered carefully so visitors can glimpse the feeling of a space before stepping into it. We invite you to wander through it. And if there's a clique you adore&mdash;or one you believe deserves a place in this growing canvas&mdash; please share it with us . Let the colors continue to blend. Scripta Manent Posted on 03 Feb '26 filed under Fanlisting , New I am pleased to announce the opening of a new fanlisting, focused on the subject of quotes&mdash;conceived as both an archival and aesthetic exercise . The subject felt well suited to the botanical linework style, which I've been wanting to use in a more deliberate and restrained way. Its clean lines and organic structure pair naturally with quotation—preserving language in a clear, distilled form. Scripta Manent - In developing this listing, my intention was to pursue a minimalist design philosophy without sacrificing visual interest. The layout privileges negative space and typographic balance, allowing the quoted material to remain central while maintaining an understated sense of elegance. Those who are drawn to the collection, interpretation, or quiet appreciation of quotations&mdash;across literature, media, or personal reflection&mdash;are warmly encouraged to join. This fanlisting is meant to function as a shared repository of resonant language, curated through simplicity and intention. N",
